section
  h3(id='req.is') req.is(type)

  p.
    Check if the incoming request contains the "Content-Type"
    header field, and if it matches the give mime <code>type</code>.

  +js.
    // With Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8
    req.is('html');
    req.is('text/html');
    req.is('text/*');
    // => true

    // When Content-Type is application/json
    req.is('json');
    req.is('application/json');
    req.is('application/*');
    // => true

    req.is('html');
    // => false

  p.
    Please refer to <a href="https://github.com/expressjs/type-is">type-is</a> for additional documentation or any issues and concerns.